  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[My Setup]]></title>
    <link href="http://brousalis.com/blog/2012/04/15/the-setup/"/>
    <updated>2012-04-15T19:54:00-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://brousalis.com/blog/2012/04/15/the-setup</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Inspired by <a href="http://usesthis.com/">The Setup</a>, a website filled with interviews dedicated to finding out how and what designers and developers use to get their work done. My career has only just begun, but I thought I&#8217;d share what I use.</p>

<h3>Hardware</h3>

<p>The <a href="http://www.apple.com/macbookpro/">15&#8221; MacBook Pro</a> has been my dev machine for the last few years of my life. Upgrading to an SSD drive will change your life, if you haven&#8217;t had the opportunity. As lame as it is, I splurged for a <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0054JGGGY/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=sebadewithsbl-20&linkCode=as2&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B0054JGGGY">Razer Mamba</a> mouse. You can turn off the glowing LED lights on this version, and it proves a really accurate and light weight mouse.</p>

<p>At home, I connect my laptop to a <a href="http://www.apple.com/imac/">27&#8221; iMac</a>. The resolution, sharpness and colours from this display are the best I&#8217;ve ever seen, and using any other monitor is depressing.</p>

<h3>Software</h3>

<p>I switched to <a href="http://www.apple.com/macosx/">Mac OS X</a> in 2009 after using Windows XP and <a href="http://www.ubuntu.com/">various</a> <a href="http://www.gentoo.org/">flavours</a> of <a href="http://www.debian.org/">Linux</a>. I do miss <a href="http://awesome.naquadah.org/">Awesome</a> window manager, as I prefer never to use my mouse, but by using some special keybindings and apps I can emulate it well enough on Lion.</p>

<p>All of my developing and editing is done in <a href="http://vim.org">VIM</a>. The learning curve is very high, but once you&#8217;ve got the hang of it - there&#8217;s no looking back. I use <a href="http://iterm.com">iTerm</a> with zsh and some heavily modified <a href="http://github.com/brousalis/dotfiles">dotfiles</a> for absolutely everything. I use <a href="http://reeder.com">Reeder</a> for my daily RSS feeds, and use <a href="http://gmail.com">Gmail</a> for all of my busy work. For mocking and design, I use <a href="http://adobe.com">Photoshop CS6</a>, shockingly.</p>

<p>This site is run on <a href="http://octopress.org">Octopress</a>, a static-site generator, turning markdown posts into what you see right now. I use <a href="http://typekit.com">TypeKit</a> for all of the fonts, and the one you are most likely seeing is <em>Proxima Nova</em> (sans) and <em>Adele</em> (serif).</p>
]]></content>
